#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:28
msgid ""
"Features are widely used as a way to do things like reduce dependency count, "
"gate `std` or `alloc`\\-dependent parts of code, or hide unstable API. Use "
"is so common that many larger crates wind up with tens of feature gates, "
"such as [`tokio`](https://docs.rs/crate/tokio/latest/features) with 24. "
"Despite being a first class component of crate structure, there are some "
"limitations that don't have elegant solutions:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:34
msgid ""
"Documentation is difficult, often requiring library authors to manually "
"manage a table of descriptions"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:36
msgid ""
"There is no way to deprecate old features, as a way to help crates maintain "
"semvar compliance"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:38
msgid "Features cannot be hidden from use in any way"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:40
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes a plan that add that information to `Cargo.toml`, solving "
"these problems."
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:43
msgid "Guide-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:47
msgid ""
"Usage is simple: features will be able to be specified as a table, instead "
"of just a dependency array. This sample section of `Cargo.toml` shows new "
"possibilities:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:51
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[features]\n"
"# Current configuration will continue to work\n"
"foo = []\n"
"# New configurations\n"
"bar = { enables = [\"foo\"], doc = \"simple docstring here\"}\n"
"baz = { enables = [\"foo\"], public = false}\n"
"qux = { enables = [], deprecated = true }\n"
"quux = { enables = [], deprecated = { since = \"1.2.3\", note = \"don't use "
"this!\" } }\n"
"\n"
"# Features can also be full tables if descriptions are longer\n"
"[features.corge]\n"
"enables = [\"bar\", \"baz\"]\n"
"doc = \"\"\"\n"
"# corge\n"
"\n"
"This could be a longer description of this feature\n"
"\"\"\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:71
msgid ""
"The `enables` key is synonymous with the existing array, describing what "
"other features are enabled by a given feature. For example, `foo = [\"dep:"
"serde\", \"otherfeat\"]` will be identical to `foo = { enables = [\"dep:"
"serde\", \"otherfeat\"] }`"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:76
msgid "All other keys are described in their individual RFCs."
msgstr ""

