#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:103
msgid ""
"Features like `aho-corasick`, `memchr`, or `use_std` would likely be `public "
"= false` since they aren't listed on the crate landing page."
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:106
msgid "Reference-level explanation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:110
msgid ""
"`enables` will take the place of the feature dependency array that currently "
"exists. Semantics will remain unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:113
msgid ""
"This is a required key. If there are no requirements, an empty list should "
"be provided (`enables = []`). This content is already in the index."
msgstr ""

#: src/3416-feature-metadata.md:116
msgid ""
"The availability of this new syntax should not require an MSRV bump. This "
"means we need to make sure that if you use `feature_name = []` in your "
"`Cargo.toml`, then the published `Cargo.toml` should as well. However, we "
"leave it as an implementation detail whether using `feature_name = { enables "
"=[] }` requires an MSRV bump for users of your published package as we have "
"not been actively streamlining the workflow for maintaining separate "
"development and published MSRVs."
msgstr ""

